description: These crispy zucchini fries are real veggie treat served with tomato salsa for dipping.
keywords: Chips & fries,Zucchini,Halal,Seafood free,Soy free,Tree nut free,Sesame free,Peanut free
name: Baked Zucchini Fries Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat the oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. In a large bowl, toss the zucchini matchsticks with the flour and salt.
Beat the eggs in a small bowl and in a shallow dish, whisk the panko breadcrumbs, garlic powder and parmesan together.
Take each matchstick, dust off any excess flour, dip in egg then breadcrumbs, turning to coat all sides and place on a baking sheet. Repeat until all matchsticks are coated.
Drizzle with olive oil and add cracked black pepper. Bake for 20 minutes, until crisp and golden.
